 Firewall Configuration on Fedora (FedoraServer Zone)

1. Check if Firewalld is running
sudo systemctl status firewalld


2.Check active zone
sudo firewall-cmd --get-active-zones


3. List current firewall settings
sudo firewall-cmd --zone=FedoraServer --list-all

Default services often include:
services: cockpit dhcpv6-client ssh


4. Add HTTP and HTTPS services
sudo firewall-cmd --zone=FedoraServer --add-service=http --permanent
sudo firewall-cmd --zone=FedoraServer --add-service=https --permanent


5. Reload firewall to apply changes
sudo firewall-cmd --reload


6. Verify the changes
sudo firewall-cmd --zone=FedoraServer --list-all


You should now see:
services: cockpit dhcpv6-client ssh http https

which means the firewall now allows:

SSH  ..... Secure remote login
HTTP  ..... Web traffic
HTTPS  ..... Secure web traffic
 defaults (cockpit, dhcpv6-client)
Added Fedora firewall setup guide


